"We are pleased to announce that on July 26, Yerevan-Rostov-na-Donu flights were able to return home to 106 Russians," TASS said in a statement.
The embassy noted that the process of registration and landing of passengers on the flight was coordinated by diplomats.
Since the introduction of restrictions on flights from Armenia, 2822 Russian citizens have been taken out.
At the same time, on July 24, Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin announced the opening of air communication with a number of countries from August 1.
