Degtyarev surprised by information about the purchase of gas "Sakhalin-1" for dollars
The interim governor of Khabarovsk region Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with the residents of Soviet Havana was surprised that the region is buying Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas for dollars.
U.S. gas is legalized in dollars until 2025.
"To be honest, I didn't know that, and I'm in a knockdown like this because of this information.
I had no idea what was still possible in Russia in 2020,” RIA Novosti quoted him as saying.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Russian Minister of Energy Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The governor also strongly stressed that by 2025 Gazprom will switch to the supply of Russian TPPs and capacities, which means that the Russian gas purchased in rubles will be used "at normal prices".
The Sakhalin-1 project is implemented through a product division agreement, where the project operator with a share of 30% is Exxon Neftegas Ltd, another 20% at Rosneft, the Japanese Sodeco - 30% and the Indian ONGC - 20%.
Khabarovsk region has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
