Woman dumped her husband's body in a pit and poured concrete under Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, a woman confessed to the murder of her own husband, which she dumped in the waste pit and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional administration of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect has been married to the deceased since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel the woman decided to murder.
“When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his hands and legs, put a polyethylene bag on his head and pressed the pillow.
When the husband stopped giving signs of life, she turned the body into a blanket, took it out to the yard and hid it in a burial pit.
The next day I called the concrete sink and poured it with concrete,” the administration said.
The woman later reported that the husband was missing.
The relatives of the deceased turned to the police, who opened the hole and pulled out the body.
The investigation is intended to ask the court for the arrest of the suspect.
The criminal case is currently under investigation.
